1. cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses a novel gate design for reversible logic, which is an emerging technology in the field of digital VLSI circuit design. 
2. cs.AR (Architecture): The paper focuses on the design of reversible adder circuits, which is a key component of digital circuit architecture. 
3. cs.DC (Digital Circuits): The paper deals with the design of digital circuits, specifically reversible adder circuits. 
4. cs.EM (Electromagnetics): The paper mentions low power consumption, which is related to the electromagnetic properties of the circuit. 
5. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper discusses the design of logic gates for reversible logic, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
